WHITE SPOT SYNDROME, SHRIMP - BRAZIL
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 1 Nov 2016, 12:54 AM
Source: Undercurrent News [edited]
https://www.undercurrentnews.com/2016/11/01/white-spot-disease-outbreak-leads-to-shrimp-price-hike-in-brazil/


A white spot shrimp disease outbreak in Brazil has led to a price hike of 50 per cent since the beginning of the year as local production has fallen nearly 30 per cent, officials say. According to the Brazilian newspaper Folha de Sao Paolo, the disease outbreak has hit the production centers of Rio Grande do Norte and Ceara. While last year's [2015] countrywide production topped 76 000 metric tons, in 2016, the total is unlikely to surpass 60 000 tons.

According to the Brazilian Association of Shrimp Farmers, known by its Portuguese acronym ABCC, prices have risen from BNR 14.50 per kilogram (USD 4.56) to BNR 21.00/kg since the beginning of the year [2016].

The lack of local production has caused issues for restaurants. "The lack of shrimp is a serious problem in Brazil. It was aggravated by disease but it is a historical issue," Paul Solmucci, president of the Brazilian Association of Bars and Restaurants said.

